ODM leader Raila Odinga is no doubt one of the few Kenyan politicians who have enjoyed the support of millions of Kenyans. The ODM leader, who has vied for the presidency four times, has turned out to be a formidable candidate whenever he vies for the top seat. The August 9 elections is not an exception. Opinion polls have lately put him second to deputy president William Ruto, a clear show of his dominance. Behind his campaign team for the August 9, elections is a team of influential women (as illustrated above) who have been at the forefront in campaigning for him.